reviewText: Excellent series, I hope it is renewed.

Season one was good, but season two was OUTSTANDING.  The addition of Wes Studi was fantastic.  I am praying for a graphic novel - like they do for when the characters were younger - to wrap up the cliffhangers.
Awesome sad it's not on anymore
Season 1 & 2 are both worth watching. Course I like anything with Jason Momoa.
Love it

SPOILER ALERT---I LOVE this show and was really bummed when I heard it was canceled. This show is intelligently written with continually good character development--things you don't see on many tv shows these days and those shows stay on for years. Go figure. There are so many story lines to use in one or two more seasons but more importantly, they have to make a season 3 or even a tv movie so viewers can see whether Junior and Marie live or die!!?? Will Phillip finally get a break that lasts? And more importantly I just want to see more Jason Momoa on tv again--in addition to the movies! Come on SundanceTV!!
Love Jason Momoa, so love the show.
Awesome series! I was disappointed that they cancelled the third season leaving the fans hanging wondering the fate of some of the key characters.
After watching season 1 I could hardly wait for season 2 to come out. It is a great series. Raw and full of intriges and twists

You need to watch this show. I was hooked immediately. I am so bummed that it was cancelled, I guess they just didn't reach their Core Audience, but man, this was an amazing ride. Strong characters that were developing, and friendships and relationships that were forming.
